description: Check the new tariff quotas amending Regulation No 1388/2013 for certain agricultural and industrial products.

details.body:
New tariff quotas for certain agricultural and industrial products amending Regulation No 1388/2013

Council Implementing Regulation No 2018/913 was published in the Official Journal, L162/3 on 27 June 2018.

New quotas come into force on 1 July 2018.

Quota period: 1 July 2018 to 31 December 2018.
Origin: NCC
Duty rate: 0%
Status: critical
Schedule quantity: Various
Documentary evidence: Certificate of Origin

Tariff quota serial number Quota period Schedule quantity Description Commodity codes
09.2726 1 July 2018 to
31 December 2018		 kg Levomenthol (INN) (CAS RN 2216-51-5) 2906 11 00 10
09.2728 1 July 2018 to
31 December 2018		 kg Ethyl trifluoroacetate (CAS RN 383-63-1) 2915 90 70 85
09.2730 1 July 2018 to
31 December 2018		 kg 4,4′-Methanediyldianiline (CAS RN 101-77-9) in form of granules, for use in the manufacture of pre-polymers 2921 59 90 80
09.2732 1 July 2018 to
31 December 2018		 kg Fluazinam (ISO) (CAS RN 79622-59-6), with a purity by weight of 98.5 % or more 2933 39 99 66
09.2734 1 July 2018 to
31 December 2018		 Pieces Plates or sheets consisting of:
- a layer of a silicon nitride ceramic with a thickness of 0.32 mm (± 0.1 mm) or more, but not more than 1.0 mm (± 0,1 mm
- covered on both sides with a foil of refined copper with a thickness of 0.8 mm (± 0,1 mm), and
- on one side partially covered with a coating of silver		 7409 19 00 20
09.2736 1 July 2018 to
31 December 2018		 kg Aluminium and magnesium alloy strip or foil:
- of an alloy conforming to standards 5182-H19 or 5052-H19
- in rolls with an outside diameter of not more than 1,350 mm
- of a thickness (tolerance – 0.006 mm) of 0.15 mm, 0.16 mm, 0.18 mm or 0.20 mm
- a camber tolerance of not more than 0.5 mm/750 mm
- a flatness measurement of I-unit ± 5
- an elongation at break of more than (5182-H19) 3 % or (5052-H19) 2.5 %
- for use in the manufacture of slats for blinds		 7607 11 90 83

Important

In any case where the information contained in this notice is at variance with that published in the official journal of the European Union the latter will reflect the correct legal position.

The HMRC Tariff, volume 1, Section 1 refers.

This information should be displayed to the public upon receipt.

No public notice or Tariff Circular will be issued.

From:

Tariff and Quota Management Team, Southend-on-Sea.

Your rights and obligations

Your Charter explains what you can expect from HMRC and what we expect from you.
